    {
      "claim": "Jaundice in Gilbert syndrome can be triggered by fasting, illness, stress, or exercise.",
      "label": "factual",
      "explanation": "These are well-established precipitants that increase bilirubin production or impair its conjugation, leading to transient jaundice."
    },
    {
      "claim": "Disorders like Dubin-Johnson and Rotor syndrome cause predominantly conjugated hyperbilirubinemia.",
      "label": "factual",
      "explanation": "These are disorders of bilirubin excretion, not conjugation, and are characterized by a rise in direct (conjugated) bilirubin."
