    {
      "claim": "The characteristic finding in Gilbert syndrome is decreased activity of hepatic UDP-glucuronosyltransferase (UGT1A1), typically to about 30% of normal.",
      "label": "factual",
      "explanation": "This is the pathophysiological hallmark of Gilbert syndrome, a genetic variant leading to reduced enzyme activity."
